      "message": "HI Ethan, one EMS and others can have max of one esr-system-info right. I believe that we need to model each tenant as one VIM object, instead of under single VIM, mutiple credentials.\n\nas a reference, in tacker aslo we followed the same approach.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 741,
        "name": "Kanagaraj Manickam",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kanagaraj.manickam@huawei.com",
        "username": "mkr1481"
      },
      "updated": "2017-09-06 06:03:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9a437d4f_3a066acf",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9a437d4f_5a736e4d",
      "file_path": "aai-schema/src/main/resources/oxm/aai_oxm_v11.xml",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 458,
      "message": "Hi Ethan, it will be like other object EMS, VNFM.\n\nHere, esr-system-info is capturing the very specific attributes of SDNC (protocol), VIM (cloud-domain, default-tenant), system-type. IMO, it is not right model instead, esr-system-info should be having only connection details, which is common for all objects VIM, EMS, VNFM and SDNC. and those properties could be, as given below and rest of the properties should be part of respective objects.:\n\n                        \"esr-system-info-id\": \"example-esr-system-info-id-val-45019\",\n                        \"system-name\": \"example-system-name-val-68461\",\n                        \"type\": \"example-type-val-3825\",\n                        \"vendor\": \"example-vendor-val-76626\",\n                        \"version\": \"example-version-val-86321\",\n                        \"service-url\": \"example-service-url-val-55636\",\n                        \"user-name\": \"example-user-name-val-77528\",\n                        \"password\": \"example-password-val-40219\",\n                        \"ssl-cacert\": \"example-ssl-cacert-val-35157\",\n                        \"ssl-insecure\": true,\n\nHope it helps to clarify my point of view. please let me know if you need any other details. thanks.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 741,
        "name": "Kanagaraj Manickam",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kanagaraj.manickam@huawei.com",
        "username": "mkr1481"
      },
      "updated": "2017-09-06 06:03:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9a437d4f_baf93aca",
      "unresolved": false
    },
